cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning control policies for a robotic mechanism in an air hockey game. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper employs a model-free deep reinforcement learning framework to learn motoric skills. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning algorithms and improving their stability. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any visual processing, but it is possible that the robot uses vision to track the puck. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category as the paper focuses more on the learning algorithm rather than the control system itself.
